## WS5 — dev-seed time-relative refactor (closes the slice-7 staleness incident)
`dev-seed.ts` now computes term windows from `new Date()`: First (prior)
[−135,−46] · **Second (current, isCurrent) [−45,+45]** · Third (next) [+46,+135]
days from today; the year brackets First.start → Third.end; `enrolledAt` =
year start. The score fixture moved off the old hardcoded First Term onto
`currentTermId` too (slice 7 deliberately left it; cp3 finishes the migration) so
gradebook + report cards AND date-resolved attendance are all populated for the
seed day. The term `update` clauses now refresh dates (re-seeds roll forward, not
just fresh resets), and a `term.updateMany(isCurrent:false)` precedes the loop —
the partial unique index `terms_school_id_current_key` (one current term/school)
would otherwise 409 when a different term is already flagged current (it did, on
the first run — the slice-7 fix had left Third Term current).
- **Verified** after `pnpm dev:seed`: TODAY 2026-06-10 falls in **Second Term**
  (2026-04-26 → 2026-07-25, isCurrent); JSS 2 A roster in the current term = 5;
  assessments in the current term = 10. The slice-7 follow-up (which lived in the
  2026-06-08 journal, not a deferred.md entry) is closed. NB: `pnpm db:seed` seeds
  ROLES only; the dev school is `pnpm dev:seed` — easy to confuse.

